Not much here yet. I'm following Notch's description of a spec for a 16-bit cpu called "dcpu" for fun.

A description can be found at: http://notch.tumblr.com/post/20056289891/start-classified-transmission.


~REGISTERS
Main:	A, B, C, X, Y, Z, I, J
System:	PC, SP, OVERFLOW


~OPCODE STRUCTURE
--------------------------
| BBBBBB | AAAAAA | OOOO |
--------------------------
0x00    0x06     0x0C   0x16
[0x00 - 0x06]:	B operand
[0x07 - 0x0C]:	A operand
[0x0D - 0x16]:	Opcode


~OPCODES
Assignment:	SET (0x1)
Arithmetic:	ADD (0x2), SUB (0x3), MUL (0x4), DIV (0x5), MOD (0x6)
Bit:		SHL (0x7), SHR (0x8)
Binary:		AND (0x9), BOR (binary-OR) (0xA), XOR (0xB)
Jump:		IFB (0xF), IFE (0xC), IFG (0xE), IFN (0xD)


~OPERANDS
[0 - 7]: 	R [A, B, C, X, Y, Z, I, J]
[8 - 15]:	M(R)
[16 - 23]:	M(M(PC + 1) + R)
[24 - 26]:	M(SP++) [POP], M(SP) [PEEK], M(--SP) [PUSH]
[27 - 29]:	S [SP, PC, OVERFLOW]
[30]:		M(M(PC + 1))
[31]:		M(PC + 1)
[32 - 63]:	Literal (0 - 31)
